Context("Numeric");
#given
$r1 = random(4,7,.1);
$r2 = random(3,4,.1);


#image scale
$imgScale =0.4;

#image aspect ratio
$width = $imgScale*979;
$height = $imgScale*686;

#computation 
$rx =($r1+$r2)*6/($r1+$r2+6);
$v1 = 24*$rx/($rx+4);
$v2 = 4*$v1/10;

#set tolerance
Context()->flags->set(
tolerance=>.01);

##############################################################
#
#  PGML 
#
#

BEGIN_PGML

[@ image( "UBC-CIR-17-003.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

In the following network, calculate the voltages [`V_1`] and [`V_2`] when [`R_1`] and [`R_2`] are [`[$r1]`] [`k\Omega`] and [`[$r2]`] [`k\Omega`], respectively.  

[`V_1=`] [_____]{"$v1"} [`V`]  
[`V_2=`] [_____]{"$v2"} [`V`]  

